hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Compute $X^2$.  Since $\tr X=0$ and $\det X=-7$, the Cayley–Hamilton theorem gives 
$$X^2-(\tr X)X+\det X\,I=0\;\Longrightarrow\;X^2-7I=0\;\Longrightarrow\;X^2=7I.$$
2.  The exponential of a $2\times2$ traceless matrix obeys
$$\exp(tX)=I\cosh(t\sqrt7)+\frac{X}{\sqrt7}\sinh(t\sqrt7).$$
3.  Hence the $(1,2)$–entry is
$$g_{12}(t)=\bigl[\exp(tX)\bigr]_{12}
=\frac{\sinh(t\sqrt7)}{\sqrt7}\,X_{12}
=\frac{\sinh(t\sqrt7)}{\sqrt7}\cdot1
=\frac{\sinh(t\sqrt7)}{\sqrt7}.$$
4.  At $t_0=\frac{\ln5}{\sqrt7}$ we have $t_0\sqrt7=\ln5$, so
$$g_{12}(t_0)=\frac{\sinh(\ln5)}{\sqrt7}
=\frac{e^{\ln5}-e^{-\ln5}}{2\sqrt7}
=\frac{5-\tfrac15}{2\sqrt7}
=\frac{24/5}{2\sqrt7}
=\frac{12}{5\sqrt7}.$$
